line_1: Coxcombs prefer the tickling sting of snuff;
line_2: Yet all their claim to wisdom is — a puff:

line_1: Tho' all his features were not grim'd with snuff.
line_2: But Michael Cassio might be drunk enough,

line_1: He shifted his trumpet, and only took snuff.
line_2: When they talk'd of their Raphaels, Corregios and stuff,

line_1: Dangling his cane about, and taking snuff,
